headline: 3 Reasons MET is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since January 2025, MetLife has been in a holding pattern, posting a small loss of 2.5% while floating around $78.24. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 7.5% gain during that period.
